<br>
I swear, people think us cattle-ranchers and dairy-cow handlers are all a bunch of inbred cruel unfeeling bastards.  <br>
<br>
I'll tell you, there were nights in the winter when we brought our calves IN THE HOUSE because it was too cold for them.  We spend hundreds of thousands of dollars building heated sheds to keep those animals all toasty warm when it's -70 degrees outside with the windchill.  <br>
<br>
When I was growing up on the ranch (yes, we had a large herd of about 5000 cattle) we treated those animals with the utmost care.  And cows are not sentient, unless you count &quot;hey guys, lets go jump in the river since we can't swim&quot; a sentient thought.  <br>
<br>
Don't get me wrong, I love my animals.  I loved my cows when I had them.  I gave them cute names like Cutlet and T-bone, cuz I didn't want to get too attached, but hell who can't get attached to a lovable animal that would slobber all over you when they got excited?  Really, I loved them.<br>
<br>
But growing up on a ranch, I knew those animals were for one thing.  Food, and producing more food.  That's the way it is.<br>
You come to know that no matter how much you loved them, that animal was gonna die in one way or another.  Leave 'em in the wild, they die.  Raise 'em on a ranch, they die.  It's incredibly inhumane to not milk a Jersey.  That bag full of milk F'ing HURTS.  Suffering?  You bet your arse they are.  Roll up your sleeves and milk that cow, dammit!<br>
<br>
These animals have been bred for one purpose, sad but true.  They are INCAPABLE of caring for themselves because of that.  So we care for them, and in the end, we kill them quickly and quietly.  <br>
<br>
I've seen the video-clips of slaughterhouse practices gone wrong.  I know what you've all seen when you refer to &quot;the sanctioned murder of innocent animals&quot;.  Here's a news flash though.  What you've seen is a RARE OCCURANCE.  It's propaganda, hyped and exploded to increase the shock value.  Check things out yourself if you don't believe me.  <br>
<br>
Truly, I could care less what you eat, and I'm probably going to turn a deaf ear when you tell me what to eat.  I enjoy my steak and my cauliflower.  I like my roast with potatoes and carrots.  I'll eat a green salad with my burger, thank you.<br>
<br>
As is the case with all walks of life, you have your extremists and your &quot;Hey man, I just wanna do my thing&quot; type of people.  Food, well why should it be different?  <br>
<br>
Vegans, kudos to you for your well-thought out and informed life choice.  Bite into that head of lettuce and feel great doing it.<br>
<br>
Omnivores, you munch away on that chunk o'meat and snarf down those veggies.  Enjoy yourselves.<br>
<br>
Just don't mix, for the love of God.  Discussions like this get under everyone's skin.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
