<br>
Humans are NOT the top of the food chain.  In our “natural” environment, the great cats and larger canids are a bit higher up on the pyramid than we are.  It so happens that we have been largely able to take ourselves out of that particular Darwinian contest, but don’t mistake that achievement as a justification to label yourself a carnivore – you’re not.<br>
<br>
And of course, the whole “food chain” image is just a convenience anyway.  Being at the top or bottom of it is not something to be sought or avoided – it simply occurs.<br>
<br>
Next, the taste thing: humans taste bad to sharks because we are not the sharks’ natural prey, not because of some evolved “bad taste”.  We certainly taste just fine to lions, and have for millions of years.  We also taste pretty good to a wide range of other animals, from mosquitoes to vultures to wolves to – so it is said – other humans.<br>
