The moronic claim of the extemest about dairy cows is a good one. A dairy cow will DIE horribly and painfully if someone DOESNT milk it. But milk is bad? It is a little late to try and save a milk cow from its fate, it was breed to do exactly what it does, provide milk.<br>
<br>
And milk must be good anyway, since it is made form vegetable matter anyway, right? So all diary products made from milk are vegetarian arent they? Dont answer it is a rhetorical question. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/usyllestraefv.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Syllestrae FV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderating inconsistently<br>since Jun 2002</span><br>  Posts: 1274<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(9/24/02 11:31:32 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1430.topic&index=72>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_supermad.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Vegans can eat me!</span><hr size=1> Don't they call it a food web or something like that now?  (-vs- food chain)<br>
